{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoder for the Cambium green-tree snapshot format."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:20CambiumSerialization20GreenSnapshotDecoderO","modules":[{"name":"Cambium"}],"title":"GreenSnapshotDecoder","symbolKind":"enum"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Decoded trees carry a freshly-minted ","type":"text"},{"code":"TokenKeyNamespace","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that is not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shared with any builder cache. This is fine for read-only consumption","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(analysis tools, AST printers, wire-format transport) and for one-shot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"decode-then-discard workflows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Load-then-edit caveat."}]},{"text":" If the decoded tree will subsequently feed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"GreenTreeBuilder.reuseSubtree(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from an incremental-parse loop, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"first reuse pays a one-time ","type":"text"},{"code":".remapped","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" slow path: the source resolver’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"namespace doesn’t match any builder’s cache, so dynamic token keys are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"re-interned and the subtree is rebuilt. After that first reparse, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"new tree’s resolver carries the cache’s namespace, and subsequent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reuses fast-path normally."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The total work is the same either way (one O(N) walk in either decode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or first-reuse). A cache-aware "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"decodeBuildResult"},{"type":"text","text":" that moves the cost"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into the load step is technically straightforward but is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"deferred"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"until a real parser\/editor consumer measures the first-edit latency"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and decides the rebalance is worth the API surface. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SubtreeReuseOutcome"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reuseSubtree"},{"type":"text","text":" is the diagnostic signal: a high "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".remapped"},{"type":"text","text":" rate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"across reparses means the cache lineage is broken (either by this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"decoder or by a missing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"result.intoCache()"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder\/decodeSnapshot(_:as:)","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSerialization\/GreenSnapshotDecoder\/decodeTree(_:as:)"],"anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Type Methods"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["